  "description": "Admin landing redirects to the system architecture view (/admin/architecture). The page documents the unified-runner architecture for the qontinui-web app: a lightweight cloud backend (auth, users, projects, storage, config sync) talking over HTTP/WebSocket to a local qontinui-runner process that owns all heavy compute (Playwright web extraction, OpenCV/template-matching vision, SAM/CLIP/OCR ML models, HAL screen capture, state-machine traversal). The view is organized as tabbed panels (Overview, Runner Detail, Data Flow, Ports & Services) and is intended for operators/admins inspecting how the platform is wired together. Assertions cover only the account-independent landing panel (/admin/architecture, default Overview tab) — section headings, the tablist + tab labels, the panel container, and the static diagram headings. No data-driven content (agent rows, dataset counts, device lists) is asserted.",
